						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone in the temple of Īśvara.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1165.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka [10]87, Pārthiva, Mārgaśira Śu. Shashṭhi, Friday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1165 November 11.</hi> The week-day was <hi rend="bold">Thursday.</hi></p>						

						<p>It states that on the above-mentioned date, <hi rend="bold">Eṟabōva of Mugudūr</hi> died in a cattleraid. He is stated to be the servant of <hi rend="bold">Eācha-gauṁḍa</hi> of Mugudūr. </p>						

						</summary>
